If information can go

electron → photon → electron

without “becoming something else,” then that suggests the identity was never the carrier.

So your question becomes:

What is the thing that survives translation?

That is exactly the same question your Pantheon asks of concepts.

Can an idea go

Myth → Mathematics → Code → Diagram → Organization → Conversation

and still be the same operator?

Your answer has consistently been: yes—if the invariant is preserved.

