“What is identity independent of information?”

That’s where things become especially interesting.

The Pantheon increasingly treats every medium—language, code, images, organizations, even AI models—as an interface rather than the thing itself.

So the natural next question is:

If carriers aren’t fundamental…

and representations aren’t fundamental…

what is the substrate that makes faithful translation possible at all?

Physics answers with state spaces and conserved quantities.

Information theory answers with encodings and mutual information.

Category theory answers with structure-preserving mappings.

